<subSubSection pageId="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,431]" pageId="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,153,179]" pageId="8">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bílý &amp; Plachetka" authorityYear="2019" box="[576,663,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucifera">
<emphasis box="[576,663,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="8">lucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ˮ refers to the bright and contrasting colouration and it is derived from the Latin substantive “ 
<emphasis box="[404,438,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="8">lux</emphasis>
ˮ (light) and verb “ 
<emphasis box="[658,723,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="8">ferere</emphasis>
ˮ (to carry).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,431]" pageId="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,454,224,251]" pageId="8">Diferential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Plachetka" authorityName="Bílý &amp; Plachetka" authorityYear="2019" box="[462,936,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucifera" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Merocratus">
<emphasis box="[462,563,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="8">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[581,711,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="8">Merocratus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[729,816,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="8">lucifera</emphasis>
Plachetka
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[949,1040,225,251]" pageId="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[949,1040,225,251]" pageId="8" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1944" box="[1217,1436,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insulaecola" subGenus="Merocratus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1241,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="8">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1259,1290,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="8">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1307,1436,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="8">insulaecola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group being most similar (and probably related) to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bily" authorityYear="1996" box="[808,943,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jakli" subGenus="Merocratus">
<emphasis box="[808,832,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="8">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[847,878,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="8">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[893,943,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="8">jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[957,1021,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1871,1896]" captionTargetBox="[205,1387,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[201,1387,166,1859]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Subgen. Merocratus (dorsal view). 1—Anthaxia (M.) jakli Bílý, 1996, holotype, 6.2 mm; 2—A. (M.) miranda Deyrolle, 1864, male (Kalimantan), 5.1 mm; 3—A. (M.) miranda, female (Johor), 7.0 mm; 4—A. (M.) angustata Bílý, sp. nov., holotype, 5.4 mm; 5—A. (M.) priska Bílý, sp. nov., holotype, 4.0 mm; 6—A. (M.) priska Bílý, sp. nov., allotype, 4.6 mm; 7—A. (M.) violaceidorsis Bílý, sp. nov., holotype, 5.0 mm; 8—A. (M.) lucifera Plachetka, sp. nov., holotype, 7.0 mm; 9—A. (M.) lucifera Plachetka, sp. nov., allotype, 7.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557861/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) from which it differs (except for the distribution) slightly by the colouration (pronotum in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bily" authorityYear="1996" box="[758,896,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jakli" subGenus="Merocratus">
<emphasis box="[758,782,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="8">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[799,830,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="8">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[846,896,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="8">jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is bright blue-green with two large, black spots and underside bright blue-green with violet abdominal ventrites in male), by the different pronotal sculpture (almost entire surface with transverse rugae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bily" authorityYear="1996" box="[585,715,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jakli" subGenus="Merocratus">
<emphasis box="[585,609,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="8">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[618,649,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="8">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[665,715,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="8">jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and slightly by the form of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1237,368,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,748,773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,174,724]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,166,729]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. Subgen. Merocratus (aedeagi, schematically, not in scale). 10—Anthaxia (M.) jakli Bílý, 1996, holotype; 11—A. (M.) miranda Deyrolle, 1864 (Kalimantan); 12—A. (M.) angustata sp. nov., Bílý, holotype; 13—A. (M.) priska Bílý, sp. nov., holotype; 14—A. (M.) violaceidorsis Bílý, sp. nov., holotype; 15—A. (M.) lucifera Plachetka, sp. nov., holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557863/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Figs. 15</figureCitation>
vs. 10).
</paragraph>
